Oman Oil Refineries & Petroleum
Industries SAOC shortlisted four banks to advise on the
expansion of the Sohar refinery and a refinancing of debt, the
 Oman Observer  reported, citing unidentified people familiar with
the plans.  The company would need as much as $3 billion in financing
for both projects, according to the newspaper. A financial
adviser will be selected in the third quarter, the report said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
